  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The current trial will provide important data on the recurrence rates and patterns of failure
      using state of the art target agent, chemotherapy and proton beam technology for patients
      with Locally Advanced Pancreatic Cancer (LAPC). A median survival of 10 months or greater
      would be considered evidence of a regimen potentially worthy of further study as a new
      treatment paradigm in one arm in a future phase III trial.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
